인태리어와 분위기는 좋습니다. 시내인것을 감안하더라도 점심에 한적하여서 시끄러운것을 싫어한다면 추천할만한 집입니다. 음식은 깔끔하게 나오나 가격대비 만족감이 떨어지고 고기의질도 그냥 그랫습니다. 밥종류는 양이 적지는 않은데, 면종류는 양이 많이 부족했습니다. 음료수도 별로 였고 서비스도 별로였는데 서비스비를 많이 때가서 별로 였던 집입니다. 다만 가게환경이나 음식이 깔끔하고 사람이 많이 없엇던 점은 좋았습니다.

result.name: AEON Tsuen Wan Store

reviews.text: Level 3 top level has a little games section for the kids. Well priced toys. Clothing is average. Lots of nice looking food and great range on the lower floor.
Good dept store. Very complete. Fresh fruit and veggies.

Don't go there on Wednesdays! Crazy place...

They have good sales after 6pm or so. I usually go there once or twice a week after work, as it's conveniently next to the mtr station and not that big of a detour. 
I especially like their pre-packaged rices, it's only 12HKD and I can get either 2 big portions or 3 smaller portions from one pack. 
Only two downsides are that it doesnt have the same product variety or cheap veggies/fruits as the one in Lai Chi Kok and that most labels are only in chinese so I dont know what the heck I am looking at :D
It is a 4 storey japanese-styled department store. Supermarket,  home appliances, electronic goods, an baby apparatus are located on various floor with accessible facilities for disabilities
A huge supermarket in Tsuen Wan. Is modern and convenient.
